 Several offices caught fire after one of the storerooms was set alight. A team of officials from the Infrastructure Directorate has been sent to the school to assess the damage and advise the Department on the course of action that needs to be undertaken, going forward. A case of arson has been opened with the police and investigations are underway. The Department requests anyone with information that could assist in the apprehension of the perpetrators to contact the police or the department at 0800 203 116.    Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za